{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=o|ぎょう}}

{{IPAchar|/ɡepu/}} → {{IPAchar|/ɡefu/}} → {{IPAchar|/ɡeu/}} → {{IPAchar|/ɡjoː/}}

From {{bor|ja|ltc|sort=きょう'|-}} {{ltc-l|業}}.  The [[漢音#Japanese|kan'on]], so likely a later borrowing.

{{ja-noun|ぎょう|hhira=げふ}}

# [[work]], [[task]], [[business]]: the [[job]] [[at hand]]
# [[profession]], [[business]], [[trade]]: what one does to [[earn a living]]
# [[studies]], [[scholarship]] (the act of being a [[scholar]]), the [[arts]]
#: {{ja-usex|医%科の'''業'''に着%手する|い%か の '''ぎょう''' に ちゃく%しゅ する|set to '''studying''' medicine, start one's medical '''studies'''}}

{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=o|ごう}}

{{IPAchar|/ɡopu/}} → {{IPAchar|/ɡofu/}} → {{IPAchar|/ɡou/}} → {{IPAchar|/ɡoː/}}

From {{bor|ja|ltc|sort=こう'|-}} {{ltc-l|業}}.  The [[呉音#Japanese|goon]], so likely an earlier borrowing.  Translation from the Sanskrit term {{m|sa|कर्मन्|tr=kárman||act, action, performance}}.

{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|なり}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=なり|-}}.  Appears in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'', completed some time after 759 CE.<ref>{{RQ:Manyoshu|5|805}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man5Yos.html#801 here]</ref>

Derived as the {{m|ja|連用形|tr=ren'yōkei||continuative or stem form}} of verb {{m|ja|業る|tr=naru||to [[earn a living]]}}. Ultimately of same origin as verb {{ja-r|なる|to become}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

{{der-top}}
* {{ja-r|災い|わざわい}}: a [[disaster]]
{{der-bottom}}
